WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:03.280 --> 01:05.440
<i>Catch them. </i>

01:06.960 --> 01:09.360
<i>Kill them. </i>

02:45.880 --> 02:47.920
What's wrong, Ronnie?

02:51.480 --> 02:53.600
I love you, Jodie.

03:10.080 --> 03:11.680
<i>Suffolk County police. </i>
<i>May I help you?</i>

03:11.840 --> 03:13.320
<i>Everybody's dead. </i>

03:13.680 --> 03:15.360
<i>What do you mean,</i>
<i>"everybody's dead"?</i>

03:15.680 --> 03:17.520
<i>A guy come running</i>
<i>into the bar and says... </i>

03:17.680 --> 03:19.920
<i>... his mother and father are shot. </i>

03:20.160 --> 03:22.720
I've been to a lot of crime scenes,
never seen one like this.

03:22.880 --> 03:25.280
<i>Six members of the family</i>
<i>were found last night... </i>

03:26.080 --> 03:28.360
...in bed, shot...

03:28.680 --> 03:30.240
...and killed.

03:31.320 --> 03:34.840
<i>Killed were car dealer Ronald Defeo,</i>
<i>his wife and four of their children. </i>

03:35.000 --> 03:36.560
<i>The sole survivor of the family... </i>

03:36.720 --> 03:38.880
<i>... 23-year-old</i>
<i>Ronald "Butch" Defeo Jr... </i>

03:39.040 --> 03:40.880
<i>... is said to have discovered</i>
<i>the bodies. </i>

03:41.040 --> 03:42.960
<i>The police state</i>
<i>that for his own safety... </i>

03:43.120 --> 03:45.200
<i>... they're holding him</i>
<i>in protective custody. </i>

03:45.360 --> 03:48.000
<i>Five of the victims were found</i>
<i>shot facedown on their beds. </i>

03:48.600 --> 03:50.240
The sixth was found in a closet.

03:52.080 --> 03:54.440
No one seemed to stir in their sleep.
It's strange.

03:54.600 --> 03:58.320
<i>Suffolk County police have charged</i>
<i>23-year-old Ronald Defeo Jr. </i>

03:58.480 --> 04:00.400
<i>The accused told police</i>
<i>he heard voices... </i>

04:00.560 --> 04:03.720
<i>... coming from within the house,</i>
<i>telling him to murder his family. </i>

04:17.880 --> 04:19.800
Oh, God!

04:20.320 --> 04:21.760
Damn it.

04:30.680 --> 04:32.560
Hi, Michael.

04:32.880 --> 04:34.480
Oh, hey, baby. You okay?

04:34.640 --> 04:36.560
George, what are you doing
to my mom?

04:37.320 --> 04:38.840
Nothing.

04:39.040 --> 04:40.720
- Yet.
- You perv.

04:48.320 --> 04:50.360
Come on up here, little man.

04:54.480 --> 04:56.280
You can make it.

04:56.680 --> 04:58.840
Oh, you're getting heavy.

05:03.440 --> 05:05.080
Did you meet my dad?

05:06.280 --> 05:07.880
No...

05:08.120 --> 05:09.480
...never had the pleasure, pal.

05:10.920 --> 05:12.520
Do I have to call you "Dad" now?

05:13.360 --> 05:14.920
- Guess what.
- What?

05:15.280 --> 05:17.880
- You can call me whatever you want.
- Anything?

05:18.040 --> 05:19.920
- Yep.
- Cool.

05:20.120 --> 05:21.920
- Anything.
- Cool.

05:22.080 --> 05:23.640
Yeah.

05:24.240 --> 05:26.040
- Stinky.
- Sure.

05:26.200 --> 05:27.680
- Poopy-head.
- Yeah.

05:27.840 --> 05:29.600
Crap-monkey-fart.

05:29.760 --> 05:32.920
Okay, we gotta draw the line
somewhere, pal, that does it.

05:38.240 --> 05:40.000
All right.

05:46.840 --> 05:48.880
- This sucks.
- You're not kidding.

05:49.040 --> 05:50.440
Billy.

05:50.880 --> 05:53.720
Look, maybe we'll grab you
something on the way to school.

05:53.880 --> 05:56.720
- What do you say, huh?
- I'm not hungry. I can walk to school.

05:56.880 --> 05:59.320
No, you can't, and get
your feet off the chair.

05:59.920 --> 06:01.960
I'll drop you a couple blocks away.
Nobody'd see.

06:02.120 --> 06:04.000
- Mom, I'm 12 years old.
- Before you plan...

06:04.160 --> 06:06.880
...your retirement party, we're gonna
drop you off at school.

06:07.040 --> 06:08.920
We got a big day.

06:10.440 --> 06:11.920
Why? Where are you guys going?

06:13.600 --> 06:16.200
- Mom, can you help me?
- Oh, Michael.

06:20.960 --> 06:23.000
Houses here are way out
of our price range, Kath.

06:23.200 --> 06:24.800
Not according to this.

06:24.960 --> 06:28.400
- Well, then it's gotta be true.
- Think positive, babe.

06:28.600 --> 06:31.920
I'm positive that houses here
are out of our price range.

06:34.160 --> 06:35.920
Look, when the business
is going good...

06:36.080 --> 06:37.240
...we're gonna...
- There.

06:37.400 --> 06:38.600
- What?
- That's it.

06:39.200 --> 06:40.400
- Look.
- Honey.

06:40.560 --> 06:42.280
Baby, look, 412 Ocean Avenue.

06:48.440 --> 06:50.280
- It's beautiful.
- What?

07:05.680 --> 07:08.000
Look at how friendly they are here,
honey.

07:08.200 --> 07:10.600
They get like that when they think
they'll make a sale.

07:10.760 --> 07:14.760
Let's just play it cool, Kath.
Kathy. Katherine.

07:15.440 --> 07:16.920
Or not.

07:24.160 --> 07:26.080
- Hi there.
- I'm Katherine Lutz.

07:26.240 --> 07:28.320
Well, just call me Edith.
This is your husband?

07:28.480 --> 07:30.840
- George.
- This is an amazing house.

07:31.000 --> 07:34.880
You are going to love it.
Just follow me in here.

07:35.760 --> 07:38.200
Careful on the steps there.

07:54.400 --> 07:57.400
Holy shit.

07:58.200 --> 07:59.720
Excuse me.

07:59.880 --> 08:02.160
Let me show you
the rest of the house.

08:02.920 --> 08:05.240
This... This is a mistake.

08:05.400 --> 08:06.640
How's that?

08:06.800 --> 08:08.880
No, I mean your ad in the paper.

08:10.080 --> 08:11.560
This is...

08:11.720 --> 08:13.800
It's gotta be a misprint.
I'm a contractor...

08:13.960 --> 08:16.280
...and I know what a place
like this should cost.

08:16.440 --> 08:17.680
And, you know, if this is...

08:17.840 --> 08:21.320
Well, if this is true, then this is a...
The deal of a lifetime.

08:21.680 --> 08:23.760
And what is wrong with that?

08:24.600 --> 08:27.280
- Come on.
- I love it.

08:30.440 --> 08:34.039
- There's a vibrant history here.
- Vibrant history, George.

08:34.200 --> 08:37.799
In fact, the house was built
in 1692, at least the basement.

08:38.320 --> 08:40.679
The rest of the house was added
from that foundation.

08:40.840 --> 08:43.240
It's one of the oldest Dutch Colonials
in Long Island.

08:43.400 --> 08:44.720
Wow, that's impressive.

08:44.880 --> 08:47.880
This room would be perfect
for children, if you have any.

08:48.040 --> 08:51.960
And the view's...
Well, have a look for yourselves.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.120
There's a boathouse.

08:56.280 --> 08:58.200
Oh, all you need now
is a boat, right?

08:58.360 --> 09:01.240
Actually, George has a speedboat.

09:01.800 --> 09:05.080
This place sounds
like it's made for you.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.920
And this is your basement.

09:18.080 --> 09:21.120
As you can see,
it's very spacious.

09:21.280 --> 09:23.800
It can be a game room,
a playroom.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.720
Well, let's... Let's have a look.

09:31.320 --> 09:34.200
I'll just wait up here.

09:39.600 --> 09:41.720
Yep, looks like a basement.

09:41.920 --> 09:43.840
So, what do you guys think?

09:44.000 --> 09:48.120
- I think you look foxy in that skirt.
- Will you stop it? Come on.

09:59.360 --> 10:01.360
Yes, yes, okay?

10:01.720 --> 10:04.560
It's a value. It's a value
for people with money.

10:04.760 --> 10:07.720
Okay, look, if we do this, we're
gonna be eating dry wall for a year.

10:07.880 --> 10:09.480
We deserve this, George.

10:09.640 --> 10:11.640
You deserve this.

10:11.800 --> 10:14.400
How many times you tell me
how hard you work for so little.

10:14.560 --> 10:17.120
- Kathy...
- Maybe today is the day it all pays off.

10:17.880 --> 10:19.920
- We'll make sacrifices.
- Huge sacrifices.

10:20.080 --> 10:22.960
Yeah, I understand that.
Listen, honey...

10:23.120 --> 10:25.280
...this is the life we want.

10:40.240 --> 10:42.320
- We're happy?
- Yes, we're happy.

10:42.480 --> 10:44.880
She's happy. I'm broke.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.240
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

10:48.440 --> 10:52.480
So look, I gotta ask,
what's the catch?

10:53.560 --> 10:55.800
There's always a catch.

10:57.160 --> 11:01.480
There was a tragedy, a crime...

11:01.640 --> 11:04.240
...a murder.
- I'm sorry, what?

11:04.480 --> 11:06.280
In the house?

11:07.080 --> 11:08.480
Several people, a family.

11:10.600 --> 11:12.920
But, you know, we've moved on,
the whole town.

11:13.120 --> 11:15.680
It is a distant memory now.

11:16.440 --> 11:18.560
And the house is fine.

11:18.720 --> 11:20.200
Really.

11:20.400 --> 11:22.920
Doesn't it seem kind of strange
to buy this house, honey?

11:23.080 --> 11:25.200
Well, houses don't kill people.

11:25.400 --> 11:27.600
People kill people.

11:28.800 --> 11:31.720
Just... Excuse us.

11:33.280 --> 11:35.480
Do you think we can make it work?

11:40.680 --> 11:42.400
You know what?

11:42.840 --> 11:45.880
You want it,
then we're gonna make it work.

11:46.040 --> 11:48.080
- Really?
- I'll work out of the basement...

11:48.280 --> 11:50.000
...and you can, well...

11:50.920 --> 11:52.760
...sell one of the kids.
- Hey.

11:53.400 --> 11:54.840
A little one.

12:09.200 --> 12:10.960
We're rich! We're rich!

12:11.440 --> 12:14.080
We're rich in something,
but it ain't money.

12:16.520 --> 12:17.920
Wait.

12:57.120 --> 12:59.720
- You say your prayers?
- Yep, said them twice.

12:59.960 --> 13:03.560
- What did you pray for?
- Lf I tell you, it won't come true.

13:04.600 --> 13:06.280
Why don't you tell him the truth.

13:06.440 --> 13:08.840
- What?
- Praying doesn't do any good.

13:09.240 --> 13:10.600
William.

13:10.800 --> 13:14.200
Nobody answered me when
I asked for Dad to be kept alive.

13:16.240 --> 13:18.120
Don't say that.

13:22.440 --> 13:25.320
Sometimes things happen in life
that can't be explained, Billy.

13:31.160 --> 13:32.720
Billy, look at me.

13:34.120 --> 13:36.880
I need you to give George
a chance, okay?

13:37.920 --> 13:41.000
You're not being disloyal
to Dad by liking George.

13:42.320 --> 13:44.840
He doesn't want to be anything
but your friend...

13:45.400 --> 13:47.160
...and maybe one day
something more.

13:47.720 --> 13:50.640
Nobody will ever
replace your dad, honey.

13:53.000 --> 13:54.600
For you too?

13:55.360 --> 13:56.920
For me too.

14:11.760 --> 14:13.400
How's Billy?

14:13.880 --> 14:15.480
He'll be fine.

14:16.880 --> 14:18.920
- First call.
- First call.

14:21.560 --> 14:24.880
- Lutz residence, how may I help you?
<i>- Can I talk to my daughter, please?</i>

14:25.160 --> 14:29.240
Yeah, sure, she's...
She's right here. Okay.

14:29.560 --> 14:32.040
Your mother's gotta stop
gushing over me, seriously.

14:32.200 --> 14:34.040
It's embarrassing now.

14:34.560 --> 14:36.280
<i>Hello?</i>

14:37.000 --> 14:40.000
- Hey, Ma.
<i>- Hi. </i>

14:40.280 --> 14:42.400
No, we're all moved in.

14:44.440 --> 14:46.480
- Yeah, Ma.
- Are you cold?

14:48.640 --> 14:50.400
No, Ma.

14:51.240 --> 14:52.080
Yeah.

16:52.160 --> 16:55.120
- What is it, baby?
- Nothing.

16:56.760 --> 16:59.640
- Are you okay, baby?
- No.

17:00.200 --> 17:02.040
I don't feel well.

17:16.960 --> 17:18.839
- Give me a kiss.
- I can do it, I can do it.

17:19.000 --> 17:20.440
No, you can't.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.599
Come here, come here.

17:25.400 --> 17:28.160
Honey, I'm gonna
make you some tea.

17:35.480 --> 17:38.400
How many brothers and sisters
do you have?

17:41.160 --> 17:43.880
- Chelsea?
- Hey, Mommy.

17:44.040 --> 17:46.200
Hi, hon. Who are you talking to?

17:46.360 --> 17:49.800
- The girl who lives in my closet.
- Oh, yeah?

17:49.960 --> 17:52.160
- And what's her name?
- Jodie.

17:53.120 --> 17:56.520
You know there are plenty of other
little girls to play with in town too?

17:56.680 --> 17:58.840
I know, but Jodie says
they're all mean.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.080
Is that Jodie?

18:07.520 --> 18:09.920
No, that's someone else.

18:10.080 --> 18:11.520
Who?

18:11.680 --> 18:14.320
I'm not supposed to say who.

18:16.080 --> 18:18.480
She says it's an A-hole.

18:18.680 --> 18:21.040
You are not allowed
to say that word.

18:40.440 --> 18:42.520
George, George.

18:42.960 --> 18:45.600
- Look what I found.
- What is that? Where'd you find that?

18:45.760 --> 18:46.960
Harry and I found it.

18:47.840 --> 18:50.080
- Where?
- In the basement.

18:50.640 --> 18:52.120
Not the basement.

18:52.280 --> 18:54.280
My office.

18:55.960 --> 18:58.320
You listen to me.
You don't go down there.

18:59.040 --> 19:00.560
Understand?

19:07.920 --> 19:10.520
Guys, would you help me
with the groceries?

19:12.360 --> 19:14.680
Go on, go help your mom.

19:19.480 --> 19:21.240
I'm sorry.

19:22.800 --> 19:24.280
Go on.

19:38.120 --> 19:41.040
- How are you feeling?
- Good, good.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.640
I found a babysitter off a board
at the grocery store.

19:44.800 --> 19:46.000
Billy will love that.

19:46.160 --> 19:48.080
How about we call her
the young-adult-sitter?

19:50.600 --> 19:51.840
Where's Chelsea?

19:53.840 --> 19:55.360
Where's Chelsea?

20:04.600 --> 20:06.320
Chelsea?

20:13.640 --> 20:14.800
Chelsea?

20:15.160 --> 20:16.960
Chelsea!

20:23.040 --> 20:24.400
Chelsea.

20:24.560 --> 20:25.960
Hey, give me your hand.

20:26.280 --> 20:27.440
Give me your hand, sweetie.

20:27.640 --> 20:30.880
- Chelsea, go to George.
- Come on. Hey, give me your hand.

20:36.400 --> 20:39.000
What were you thinking?
You could have fallen in the water.

20:39.160 --> 20:41.000
Jodie wanted to see the boat.

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
Somebody should have been
watching you.

21:43.760 --> 21:46.440
Billy, get up.

21:47.000 --> 21:49.440
Billy, I gotta go pee.

24:02.400 --> 24:03.800
Chelsea.

24:46.600 --> 24:48.240
Goddamn it, Harry.

24:51.240 --> 24:53.960
Seriously. You trying to kill me?

25:58.600 --> 26:00.040
Come on, get away from there.

26:00.280 --> 26:01.960
Hey, that's enough.

26:02.440 --> 26:04.000
Hey!

26:12.320 --> 26:14.680
George? Hon, what are you
doing down here?

26:15.520 --> 26:18.640
It's the only place
that's warm in this damn house.

26:19.760 --> 26:21.800
Somebody keeps opening
the windows.

26:26.200 --> 26:27.880
What is that?

26:29.760 --> 26:31.560
You tell me.

26:33.040 --> 26:35.800
- Why don't you come back to bed.
- No, I can't sleep.

26:35.960 --> 26:37.560
I'm sorry, baby.

26:37.760 --> 26:39.440
Don't...

26:39.640 --> 26:42.240
Don't talk to me like
I'm one of your kids, okay?

26:42.400 --> 26:44.880
- What?
- That goddamn dog woke me up.

26:46.400 --> 26:48.080
Billy's dog.

26:50.000 --> 26:51.360
Found him in the boathouse.

26:52.600 --> 26:55.000
- But you locked it.
- Yeah.

26:55.160 --> 26:57.640
Hey, and guess
what I found in Billy's room.

27:05.600 --> 27:07.600
You ready to talk
about those keys?

27:07.800 --> 27:10.840
There's not a lot in this world can't
be solved with an apology, Billy.

27:11.000 --> 27:13.320
I'm not apologizing
for something I didn't do...

27:13.480 --> 27:14.720
...George.

27:25.560 --> 27:27.560
Get to work, buddy.

27:30.120 --> 27:32.520
"Get to work, buddy. "

28:00.760 --> 28:02.720
"Katch 'em... "

28:04.680 --> 28:06.400
George?

28:06.880 --> 28:08.680
George?

28:09.280 --> 28:11.280
George, you down there?

28:13.240 --> 28:14.640
George?

28:17.080 --> 28:18.240
What?

28:18.400 --> 28:19.840
What's the matter?

28:21.840 --> 28:24.080
Did you do that thing
with the magnets?

28:29.320 --> 28:31.520
Nothing. Just seeing things,
I guess.

29:00.720 --> 29:01.920
You look hideous.

29:02.080 --> 29:04.560
You're rather repulsive yourself,
Mr. Lutz.

29:04.760 --> 29:07.120
- Where's the babysitter?
- Babysitter?

29:07.320 --> 29:09.040
Told you guys,
I don't need a babysitter.

29:09.200 --> 29:11.240
- I'm old enough.
- Baby, I know you can...

29:11.400 --> 29:15.160
I'm not letting her watch us. She's
not coming in, I won't let her. I won't.

29:15.800 --> 29:17.680
- She's not coming in.
- Billy, listen to me.

29:17.840 --> 29:20.880
- I won't leave you alone.
- I can't believe you hired a babysitter.

29:21.040 --> 29:22.560
- I told you I was old enough.
- Hi.

29:22.720 --> 29:25.320
- I'm Lisa, the babysitter.
- Great.

29:25.880 --> 29:27.760
Can I take your coat?

29:28.000 --> 29:29.520
Okay.

29:31.400 --> 29:33.080
Hi.

29:34.880 --> 29:36.120
I'm Billy.

29:45.320 --> 29:47.840
You sure you don't want
a babysitter?

29:48.080 --> 29:50.000
Would you like me
to show you around?

29:50.160 --> 29:51.400
No, it's okay.

29:51.560 --> 29:54.120
I know it already.
I used to sit for the Defeos.

29:58.200 --> 30:00.000
Kind of freaky being back here.

30:00.440 --> 30:01.960
I'm Billy.

30:02.160 --> 30:04.000
Yeah, I got you the first time.

30:04.760 --> 30:06.840
Have a good night, Billy.

30:14.640 --> 30:16.560
This is just what we needed,
don't you think?

30:16.720 --> 30:19.280
Yeah. Definitely.

30:19.440 --> 30:21.280
You feeling all right?

30:21.600 --> 30:23.120
You know what?

30:23.280 --> 30:25.040
I feel better.

30:25.960 --> 30:28.320
I think I just needed
to get out of the house.

30:28.480 --> 30:30.200
Come on, drink up.

30:30.360 --> 30:32.200
Are you trying
to get me drunk, Mr. Lutz?

30:33.280 --> 30:35.440
That's the appeal of marriage, hon.

30:35.640 --> 30:37.360
Hopefully, I won't have to.

30:44.440 --> 30:46.160
Be right out.

30:56.800 --> 30:58.000
Hungry?

30:59.000 --> 31:01.000
Kid, you read my mind.

31:01.520 --> 31:02.720
The kids, they're...

31:02.880 --> 31:04.960
They're going through
a tough time.

31:05.120 --> 31:07.400
I guess they're just
adjusting to everything.

31:07.560 --> 31:09.520
Yeah, well, we all are.

31:11.320 --> 31:13.160
Do you feel different?

31:15.520 --> 31:17.120
What do you mean?

31:17.280 --> 31:18.960
About us.

31:20.560 --> 31:22.360
About me.

31:25.880 --> 31:27.080
Yeah.

31:27.240 --> 31:28.400
Yeah, I do.

31:30.320 --> 31:34.280
I feel like for the first time in my life,
I'm sure about something.

31:35.120 --> 31:36.880
And that's you.

31:38.640 --> 31:41.640
And I'm gonna spend the rest
of my life making you happy.

31:42.320 --> 31:45.080
Oh, boy, you know how
to turn on that Lutz charm.

31:55.400 --> 31:57.840
Some people say his tongue is fake.

32:00.000 --> 32:01.520
I think it's all him.

32:03.960 --> 32:05.320
Got this at a pinball arcade.

32:06.640 --> 32:08.080
Cool.

32:10.600 --> 32:12.320
So do you French?

32:12.840 --> 32:14.360
Do I what?

32:14.520 --> 32:17.000
Kissing, tongues.

32:18.880 --> 32:20.440
No.

32:21.680 --> 32:24.120
Did your family know the Defeos?

32:24.360 --> 32:27.560
- The who?
- The family that lived here before you.

32:29.920 --> 32:31.520
No, we just moved here.

32:32.280 --> 32:34.960
Well, you know what
